\dfrac{1}{\sin(\theta)}=\dfrac{2\sqrt {3}}{3}
\sin (\theta) = \dfrac{2\sqrt {3}}{3}
\sqrt 3 \csc\theta = 2 \iff \csc \theta = \frac{2}{\sqrt 3} \iff \frac 1{\sin \theta} = \frac 2{\sqrt 3}
\iff \sin\theta = \frac{\sqrt 3}2 \implies \theta =\sin^{-1}\left(\frac{\sqrt 3}{2}\right)
\dfrac1{\sin \theta} = \dfrac{2 \cdot\sqrt3}{3}
\sin \theta =\dfrac{3}{2\cdot \sqrt 3}
\sqrt 3
